# Hubly product direction

## V1 Freeze

Architecture · feature scope · AI systems — **frozen**.

No new AI systems · product categories · architecture · capabilities  
unless required to complete the V1 Finish Line.

**Hubly Brain is the only intelligence layer.**  
No direct Claude/OpenAI outside `hubly_ai.ts`.  
No new prompts · agents · parallel AI surfaces until every existing capability already uses Hubly Brain (`docs/AI_BRAIN_MIGRATION_AUDIT.md`).

Deterministic by design (not LLM): Hubly Daily · Business Health · Timeline · Owner Feed.  
AI comes after facts.

**Source of truth:** `docs/V1_FINISH_LINE.md` · `docs/LAUNCH_CHECKLIST.md` · `docs/AI_BRAIN_MIGRATION_AUDIT.md`

## North Star

**Revenue generated through Hubly-powered businesses.**

### Three success questions

1. Can a business launch?  
2. Can a customer pay?  
3. Can the owner run every day without leaving Hubly?  

## Current milestone

**First Customer** — proven with a **real production transaction**.

Do not begin Business Running until then.

DoD: hire → pay → calendar → job → complete → review → CRM → Health → Feed  
with no manual intervention.

## Ordered blockers

1. Real production payment proof (`docs/PRODUCTION_PAYMENT_PROOF.md`)  
2. Calendar reliability  
3. Complete hire lifecycle verification  
4. Reliability pass  
5. Beta readiness (10 real businesses)  

## Sprint rule

Every sprint completes one measurable customer outcome  
(booked · paid · review requested · calendar conflict prevented).

Before merge: *Could a real owner make more money because of this?*

## Never (V1)

- AI Marketing · Autonomous Growth · Living Marketplace · Advanced Coach · BI  
- Fake success when a Connection is missing  
- Dashboards before advice  
- Architecture PRs for their own sake  
